<CSSPow>
<summary>
The <strong><c>pow()</c></strong> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</see> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Functions">function</see> is an exponential function that returns the value of a base raised to the power of a number.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>The <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/exp">exp</see> function is a special case of <c>pow()</c> where the value of the base is the mathematical constant <see href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E_(mathematical_constant)">e</see>.</para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/sqrt">sqrt</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/hypot">hypot</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/exp">exp</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/log">log</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/pow"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<returns>Returns a {{CSSxRef(&amp;quot;&amp;lt;number&amp;gt;&amp;quot;)}} representing base&amp;lt;sup&amp;gt;number&amp;lt;/sup&amp;gt;, that is, <c>base</c> raised to the power of <c>number</c>.</returns>
</CSSPow>
